  <title>Download a <app>GNU/Linux</app> operating system</title>

  <p><app>GNU/Linux</app> is a kernel. A kernel is a software that connects and manages hardware to make possible the use of application software. A <app>GNU/Linux</app> based operating system along with a software packaging system is called a <em>Distribution</em>, it comes pre-packaged with various software that simplifies installation and usage. To know the various distributions available, you can browse <link href="http://distrowatch.com">Distrowatch</link> website.</p>

  <section id="why-arch">
    <title>Recommended distributions</title>

